        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 1:31PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Vivian to Greenwood. Movement was
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shreveport, Bossier City, Vivian, Greenwood, Blanchard, Waskom,
Benton, Oil City, Mooringsport, Hosston, Belcher, Ida, Gilliam, Gray,
Dixie, Caddo Lake, Cross Lake, Cavett, and Bethany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
